data.enText: to move away from the place where you should be, without intending to

data.chText: 他偏到了一辆迎面驶来的汽车的行车路线上。
data.enText: He strayed into the path of an oncoming car.

data.chText: 她的目光不时瞟向墙上的钟。
data.enText: Her eyes kept straying over to the clock on the wall.
to begin to think about or discuss a different subject from the one you should be thinking about or discussing

data.chText: 我老走神，一再回想起我们上次在一起交谈的情景。
data.enText: My mind kept straying back to our last talk together.

data.chText: 我们似乎是偏离了辩论的主题。
data.enText: We seem to be straying from the main theme of the debate.

data.chText: 有外遇；在别处拈花惹草

data.enText: to have a sexual relationship with sb who is not your usual partner

data.enText: away from home and lost; having no home

data.chText: 零星的；孤立的；离群的；走散的
data.enText: separated from other things or people of the same kind
A civilian was killed by a stray bullet .

data.chText: 走失的宠物（或家畜）；无主的宠物（或家畜）
data.enText: an animal that has got lost or separated from its owner or that has no owner

data.chText: 离群者；走散者；不在原位置的东西
data.enText: a person or thing that is not in the right place or is separated from others of the same kind

tr: an animal that has strayed (especially a domestic animal)
lose clarity or turn aside especially from the main subject of attention or course of argument in writing, thinking, or speaking
example: She always digresses when telling a story
Don't digress when you give a lecture

tr: move about aimlessly or without any destination, often in search of food or employment
example: The cattle roam across the prairie
the laborers drift from one town to the next
They rolled from town to town

tr: wander from a direct course or at random
example: The child strayed from the path and her parents lost sight of her
don't drift from the set course

tr: (of an animal) having no home or having wandered away from home

value.def: If someone strays somewhere, they wander away from where they are supposed to be.

example.ex: Tourists often get lost and stray into dangerous areas...
example.tran: 游客常会迷路并误入危险区域。

example.ex: Crews stray outside to film the view from the pavement...
example.tran: 工作人员移到人行道上拍摄这一景色。

example.ex: A railway line crosses the park so children must not be allowed to stray.
example.tran: 有一条铁路横穿该公园，因此必须禁止小孩子在附近闲逛。

value.def: A stray dog or cat has wandered away from its owner's home.

example.ex: A stray dog came up to him.
The dog was a stray which had been adopted.
example.tran: 这是条曾被收养的流浪狗。

value.def: If your mind or your eyes stray, you do not concentrate on or look at one particular subject, but start thinking about or looking at other things.

example.ex: Even with the simplest cases I find my mind straying...
example.tran: 即使在处理最简单的案例时我也老走神。

example.ex: She could not keep her eyes from straying towards him.

value.tran: 走神;(视线)偏离，往别处看

value.def: You use stray to describe something that exists separated from other similar things.

example.ex: An 8-year-old boy was killed by a stray bullet...
example.tran: 一名 8 岁男孩儿被流弹打死。

example.ex: She shrugged a stray lock of hair out of her eyes.
example.tran: 她把一缕散发从眼前甩开。
